    "intro": "Romans 3 is the doctrinal apex of the New Testament. The movements below trace its argument from the closing of the Jewish objection (3:1-8) through the universal indictment (3:9-20), the announcement of God's righteousness (3:21-26), and the first three applications (3:27-31). Each movement is meaning-first; Greek notes follow only where the original sharpens what the English carries.",
